When audio or text to speech is included on your cards, Anki will show buttons you can click on to replay the audio. If you prefer not to see the buttons, you can hide them in the preferences screen. You can customize their appearance in your card styling, for example, to make them smaller and colored, you could use the following: .replay-button svg { width: 20px; height: 20px;
}
.replay-button svg circle { fill: blue;
}
.replay-button svg path { stroke: white; fill: green;
}

